# ğŸ™ Git & GitHub Basic Commands

Git is a powerful version control system used to track changes and collaborate on projects efficiently.  
Hereâ€™s a quick list of essential **Git & GitHub commands** for your DevOps toolkit.

---

## ğŸ Initialization & Configuration

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `git init` | Initialize a new Git repository |
| `git clone <repo-url>` | Clone a repository |
| `git config --global user.name "<your-name>"` | Set global username |
| `git config --global user.email "<your-email>"` | Set global email |
| `git config --list` | Display config settings |

---

## ğŸ“‚ Working With Files

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `git status` | Show file status |
| `git add <file>` | Add file to staging |
| `git add .` | Add all files to staging |
| `git reset <file>` | Unstage a file |
| `git rm <file>` | Delete a file and stage removal |

---

## ğŸ“¦ Commit Operations

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `git commit -m "<message>"` | Commit staged changes |
| `git commit -am "<message>"` | Add & commit tracked files |
| `git log` | View commit history |
| `git log --oneline` | Short commit log |

---

## ğŸŒ¿ Branching

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `git branch` | List branches |
| `git branch <name>` | Create a new branch |
| `git checkout <branch>` | Switch to a branch |
| `git checkout -b <name>` | Create and switch |
| `git switch <branch>` | Switch (newer command) |
| `git merge <branch>` | Merge branch into current |
| `git branch -d <branch>` | Delete a branch |

---

##  Pushing & Pulling

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `git remote -v` | Show remote URLs |
| `git remote add origin <url>` | Add a remote |
| `git push -u origin <branch>` | Push and set upstream |
| `git push` | Push changes |
| `git pull` | Pull latest changes |
| `git fetch` | Fetch updates only |

---

## ğŸ”„ Reset & Revert

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `git reset --soft <commit>` | Move HEAD, keep staged changes |
| `git reset --hard <commit>` | Reset and remove local changes |
| `git revert <commit>` | Undo commit with a new commit |

---

## ğŸ“ GitHub CLI Commands

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `gh auth login` | Authenticate to GitHub |
| `gh repo create` | Create a new repository |
| `gh issue list` | List issues |
| `gh pr create` | Create a pull request |
| `gh pr merge <id>` | Merge a PR |

---

## ğŸ§¹ Cleanup

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `git clean -n` | Preview files to be deleted |
| `git clean -f` | Delete untracked files |
| `git reset --hard` | Discard all local changes |

---
## ğŸ” Rebase

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `git rebase <branch>` | Rebase the current branch onto `<branch>` (replay commits) |
| `git rebase --continue` | Continue after resolving conflicts during a rebase |
| `git rebase --abort` | Abort rebase and return to original state |
| `git rebase --skip` | Skip the current patch that failed during rebase |
| `git rebase -i <commit>` | Interactive rebase starting from `<commit>` (use `-i HEAD~n` for last n commits) |
| `git pull --rebase` | Fetch and rebase local commits on top of upstream (avoids merge commits) |
| `git rebase --onto <newbase> <upstream> <branch>` | Rebase `<branch>` onto `<newbase>`, excluding commits already in `<upstream>` |
| `git reflog` | (Handy after bad rebase) Find commit hashes to recover lost commits |
---

